1
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:15,033
<i> You want to die or what?</i>

2
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:18,567
<i>You know you're not supposed
to mix painkillers with alcohol.</i>

3
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:19,667
<i> Hazel Cruz?</i>

4
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:22,833
<i> What's that?</i>

5
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:25,933
<i>Felma filed a restraining order
against me.</i>

6
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:27,667
<i>You know what?
You're such a liar.</i>

7
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,367
<i>I know you and Felma are hiding
something.</i>

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,000
<i>What are you really doing here
with her?</i>

9
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:33,200
<i> Don't point your finger at me!</i>

10
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,700
<i> Bro! Bro! That's enough!</i>

11
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:38,133
<i>Take your friend home.
Don't make a scene here.</i>

12
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:39,400
<i> Noah!</i>

13
00:00:39,533 --> 00:00:41,367
<i> Noah, it's Felma!</i>

14
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,133
<i> Help!</i>

15
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:44,867
<i>- Noah!
- Felma!</i>

16
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,200
<i> I don't know what to do.</i>

17
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:48,733
<i>- Felma!
- Let's call an ambulance!</i>

18
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:52,467
<i>Doctor, what can we do?
Anything, please.</i>

19
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,833
<i> As long as Felma gets better.</i>

20
00:00:53,967 --> 00:00:56,700
<i>I strongly suggest surgery
as soon as possible.</i>

21
00:00:56,833 --> 00:00:58,567
<i>Felma will have surgery. Right?</i>

22
00:00:58,700 --> 00:00:59,633
<i> No.</i>

23
00:01:00,967 --> 00:01:02,233
<i> I don't want surgery.</i>

24
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:04,667
<i> I don't want it.</i>

25
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:14,433
What is this?

26
00:01:17,267 --> 00:01:18,300
Nurse!

27
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:22,067
Nurse!

28
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,033
Ma'am.

29
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:26,967
What is this? Why am I tied up?
Untie me.

30
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:29,300
We're just following
the doctor's orders.

31
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:31,000
What?

32
00:01:32,033 --> 00:01:33,067
What orders?

33
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:35,867
The doctor's orders?

34
00:01:37,567 --> 00:01:39,067
Or their orders?

35
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,833
Why did you even bring me
to the hospital?

36
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:48,567
You should've just let me die.

37
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:51,100
Isn't that what you want?

38
00:01:51,233 --> 00:01:53,033
For me to disappear
from your lives?

39
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:57,333
So I can be with Jessica.

40
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,700
Let me go. Let me go!

41
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:05,600
Take this off! Take it off!

42
00:02:05,733 --> 00:02:06,400
Friend.

43
00:02:06,533 --> 00:02:07,267
Take it off.

44
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,667
- Friend.
- Alice, what is this?

45
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:11,100
- Friend.
- Remove it. I don't want this.

46
00:02:11,233 --> 00:02:12,333
Take it off.

47
00:02:13,967 --> 00:02:15,067
This is your fault...

48
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:16,633
This is all your fault!

49
00:02:17,767 --> 00:02:20,167
You're the reason my life
is ruined!

50
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:21,800
It's your fault!

51
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:29,200
Jessica...

52
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:32,233
Jessica, my child.

53
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:35,233
Take me with you.

54
00:02:39,700 --> 00:02:41,600
I just want to be
with my daughter.

55
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:44,833
Jessica...

56
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:51,067
Felma, why won't you do it?

57
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:55,967
What if I die?

58
00:02:57,867 --> 00:02:59,933
What if I die during
the surgery?

59
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:05,000
I'm not ready to leave the kids.

60
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,633
I still want to be with you.

61
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:13,767
Felma, don't say that.

62
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:17,767
Look at me,
I couldn't even walk before.

63
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:19,600
Now I can.

64
00:03:21,933 --> 00:03:24,733
That's different.

65
00:03:27,133 --> 00:03:29,033
I'm getting surgery.

66
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:33,667
What if I don't wake up?

67
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:46,767
What if I don't leave
this hospital alive?

68
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,867
But with chemo,

69
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:58,967
I'm sure I'll still be with you
for a few more months.

70
00:03:59,133 --> 00:04:00,867
If I'm lucky,

71
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:05,567
- maybe a year or two.
- No.

72
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:09,400
Don't talk like that.

73
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,333
We still have a long time
together.

74
00:04:16,733 --> 00:04:19,133
You're only saying that.

75
00:04:19,267 --> 00:04:29,233
But the truth is, none of
us really knows what'll happen.

76
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,267
I feel sorry for the kids.

77
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,533
Just when they're finally happy

78
00:04:39,667 --> 00:04:42,267
because our family's coming
together...

79
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,633
this happens.

80
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:46,933
No, Felma.

81
00:04:48,033 --> 00:04:50,133
The kids are strong.

82
00:04:52,433 --> 00:04:55,133
So you have to be strong, too.

83
00:04:55,267 --> 00:04:56,500
For them.

84
00:04:57,767 --> 00:04:58,967
For us.

85
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:08,033
Jeff, call the police.

86
00:05:08,167 --> 00:05:09,967
Let's have Hazel arrested.

87
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:12,567
The doctor said she's under
observation, right?

88
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:17,100
Then hospital arrest.
Whatever it takes.

89
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,700
She has to stop all this evil.

90
00:05:19,833 --> 00:05:21,867
I feel somewhat sorry for her.

91
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:24,367
What?

92
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:26,633
What's gotten into you?

93
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:31,767
Yeah, why do you suddenly feel
bad for her?

94
00:05:33,067 --> 00:05:36,433
Because she has no one left.

95
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:39,233
She still has that best friend
who keeps enabling her.

96
00:05:40,167 --> 00:05:42,067
No, sis.

97
00:05:43,233 --> 00:05:45,267
Our dad left her.

98
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,400
Jessica's gone.

99
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:51,800
She lost the two people
she loved most.

100
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,967
She deserves it,
after everything she's done.

101
00:05:56,100 --> 00:06:01,067
But, sis, does she really
deserve to lose Jessica?

102
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:03,000
Okay, sure, she's evil.

103
00:06:04,267 --> 00:06:07,933
But her grief is real.

104
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:10,067
Yeah, maybe you're right.

105
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:14,667
Still, she has to pay for
violating the restraining order.

106
00:06:18,100 --> 00:06:20,633
They said no one got hurt.

107
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:21,700
Bro.

108
00:06:22,933 --> 00:06:24,133
Bro, what happened?

109
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:28,033
Bro, it's Hazel.

110
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:29,933
What did she do this time?

111
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:37,033
Dad, what should we do with her?

112
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:39,833
Go ahead, have her arrested!

113
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:42,167
Alright, I'll call the police.

114
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:49,267
Dad, is Mom there with you?

115
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:53,067
Can you turn your video on
so we can see you?

116
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:55,967
Well...

117
00:06:56,100 --> 00:06:58,433
the signal here is weak, dear.

118
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:03,133
And your mom's in a conference.

119
00:07:03,267 --> 00:07:07,767
Dad, are you sure you and Mom
are okay there?

120
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:13,000
We haven't seen you since you
arrived.

121
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:14,867
We're fine, sweetheart.

122
00:07:15,033 --> 00:07:17,733
We had some misunderstandings
at first.

123
00:07:17,867 --> 00:07:19,400
But we're okay now.

124
00:07:19,533 --> 00:07:21,133
So, Dad, when are you coming
back?

125
00:07:24,133 --> 00:07:28,467
That depends on your mom.
Probably in a few more days.

126
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,600
Let's celebrate when you get
home, okay?

127
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:33,133
Yeah, sure.

128
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:36,267
I'll tell your mom.
She'll be happy to hear that.

129
00:07:36,400 --> 00:07:37,867
Alright, bye for now.

130
00:08:18,533 --> 00:08:19,467
Noah?

131
00:08:21,333 --> 00:08:22,267
Felma.

132
00:08:23,667 --> 00:08:24,967
How are you?

133
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:26,533
Do you need anything?

134
00:08:28,567 --> 00:08:29,967
Are you in pain?

135
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,667
Thank you.

136
00:09:08,533 --> 00:09:11,367
Felma, I should get going.

137
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,500
I'll just head home for now.

138
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:19,533
If you need anything,
just call me, okay?

139
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:07,867
Coleen?

140
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,300
Wake up!

141
00:10:11,800 --> 00:10:12,833
Coleen?

142
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:20,367
Coleen!

143
00:10:22,300 --> 00:10:24,000
Andeng, what are you doing here?

144
00:10:25,033 --> 00:10:27,367
I was just trying to wake
Coleen up.

145
00:10:28,933 --> 00:10:33,033
She left early.
I thought she told you.

146
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:33,900
Wait,

147
00:10:35,100 --> 00:10:36,567
where was she going?

148
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:39,167
She still has a lot going on
at school.

149
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,767
Didang.

150
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:45,100
You know it's dangerous
to go out alone.

151
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:47,700
What are you still worried
about, Andrea?

152
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,400
Hazel has been arrested.

153
00:10:50,533 --> 00:10:52,600
So it's safe now.

154
00:10:52,733 --> 00:10:54,967
Even you can go out again.

155
00:10:55,100 --> 00:10:56,900
Just don't forget
your laundry, okay?

156
00:10:57,033 --> 00:10:58,467
I'll get it later.

157
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,733
It's in the hamper.

158
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:04,700
Alright, be careful.

159
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:21,500
Alice.

160
00:11:21,633 --> 00:11:23,367
Alice, help me.

161
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:24,767
Stop it.

162
00:11:25,867 --> 00:11:28,200
Help me escape.

163
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:30,667
You're only making things worse
for yourself.

164
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,800
Alice, please, just let me go.

165
00:11:32,933 --> 00:11:34,633
If you won't help me,
I'll do it myself.

166
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:38,400
You want to add fugitive
to your list of crimes.

167
00:11:50,700 --> 00:11:52,300
What is she doing here?

168
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:01,967
We're here to make a deal.

169
00:12:03,067 --> 00:12:05,467
What makes you think I'd make
a deal with the person

170
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,433
who killed my daughter?

171
00:12:07,567 --> 00:12:09,033
Do it for Jessica.

172
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:12,833
Do you really think she'd want
to see you in jail?

173
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:18,400
You violated the restraining
order.

174
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:21,467
You could go to prison
for up to six months.

175
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:25,300
That's on top of the penalties
you have to pay.

176
00:12:25,433 --> 00:12:26,733
So what are you going to do?

177
00:12:27,933 --> 00:12:29,667
Cancel the restraining order?

178
00:12:31,367 --> 00:12:33,300
Do you think your mistress
mom would agree

179
00:12:33,433 --> 00:12:35,067
to let me walk free?

180
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:38,233
We're her authorized
representatives.

181
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:41,633
We can file to dismiss
the restraining order.

182
00:12:43,933 --> 00:12:45,500
What do you want in return?

183
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:47,867
Stop harassing us.

184
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:57,333
Wow, you're making demands
like you're the legal family.

185
00:12:58,567 --> 00:13:00,800
Not everything legal is right.

186
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,367
Just accept it
that Dad loves Mom.

187
00:13:04,500 --> 00:13:05,367
No!

188
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:07,767
I won't accept that.

189
00:13:09,333 --> 00:13:10,800
I need Manuel.

190
00:13:10,933 --> 00:13:12,733
Do you really think
what you're doing now

191
00:13:12,867 --> 00:13:14,433
will make him forgive you?

192
00:13:14,567 --> 00:13:18,400
The more you hurt us,
the angrier he gets at you.

193
00:13:19,533 --> 00:13:21,667
If you stop bothering us,

194
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:24,100
there's a good chance Dad
will forgive you.

195
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:27,467
I'm sure all he wants
is for Jessica to be happy.

196
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:29,067
Friend.

197
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:33,100
She has a point.
Just take the deal.

198
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:35,833
Come on.

199
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:44,333
Coleen, why did you do that
without telling us first?

200
00:13:44,467 --> 00:13:46,133
Because I knew you wouldn't
agree.

201
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:47,867
Enough. Stop fighting.

202
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,667
No, because I really don't get
it.

203
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,633
Hazel tried to have you jailed

204
00:13:51,767 --> 00:13:53,067
even though you did nothing
wrong.

205
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:54,233
And yet you let her go,

206
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,067
after everything she's done
to us?

207
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,667
That was the only way
I could think of

208
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:00,467
to finally give us peace.

209
00:14:00,600 --> 00:14:03,900
That is, if she keeps her end
of the bargain.

210
00:14:04,033 --> 00:14:07,233
She never does. She's a liar.

211
00:14:07,367 --> 00:14:08,900
What about Mom?

212
00:14:09,033 --> 00:14:11,333
She's the one who filed
that restraining order.

213
00:14:11,467 --> 00:14:12,533
Does she even know?

214
00:14:13,767 --> 00:14:14,700
No.

215
00:14:15,767 --> 00:14:20,933
But I'm sure she'll understand
once I explain why I did it.

216
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,400
She has the nerve to walk out?

217
00:14:38,267 --> 00:14:40,000
<i> Hello, Dad?</i>

218
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:42,500
Hello, Coleen.
Why did you do that?

219
00:14:42,633 --> 00:14:44,400
<i> I'm sorry, Dad.</i>

220
00:14:49,167 --> 00:14:50,633
Your mom's awake now.

221
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:52,700
I'll call you back later, okay?

222
00:14:52,833 --> 00:14:55,000
Okay, Dad. Bye.

223
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,667
Who was that?

224
00:15:02,933 --> 00:15:04,000
Coleen.

225
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,533
What did she want?

226
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:09,367
Nothing.

227
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:12,367
Just asking when we're coming
home.

228
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:16,533
I miss them.

229
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:19,367
They miss you so much, too.

230
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,900
You know, Felma,

231
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:27,300
we can't hide this
from the kids forever.

232
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,200
Every day we stay here

233
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:36,267
is another lost chance
to be with them.

234
00:15:46,933 --> 00:15:48,533
Let's go home.

235
00:16:22,400 --> 00:16:26,200
Coleen's character development
is something else.

236
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:29,967
She's the one who got you
a get-out-of-jail card.

237
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:32,733
So you, too, friend.

238
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:36,200
Work on your own character
development.

239
00:16:36,333 --> 00:16:40,233
Change your life after
this second chance.

240
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:47,333
Yes, Alice.

241
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:49,900
I'm really changing.

242
00:16:51,167 --> 00:16:52,767
Because starting today,

243
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:57,233
I'm not letting Felma
and her kids beat me.

244
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:00,733
You're really crazy, friend.

245
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:21,100
This is heavy.

246
00:17:21,233 --> 00:17:23,700
Wow, that smells amazing,
sweetheart.

247
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:26,133
Chicken soup!

248
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:27,367
Of course, Auntie.

249
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,800
I really made it extra good
for Mom and Dad.

250
00:17:29,933 --> 00:17:32,433
And it's healthy, too.

251
00:17:32,567 --> 00:17:34,767
So Ma'am Felma can recover
faster.

252
00:17:36,267 --> 00:17:37,200
She's sick?

253
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:40,333
Let's eat together, Joel.

254
00:17:40,467 --> 00:17:42,133
- Yeah, homesick.
- Excuse me.

255
00:17:42,267 --> 00:17:44,067
Okay, game. One, two...

256
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,067
You're unbelievable, Didang.

257
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,800
You're so silly.

258
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,433
Sorry, sis.

259
00:17:58,567 --> 00:17:59,500
Let's try the...

260
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:00,600
what was it again?

261
00:18:00,733 --> 00:18:04,567
- Chicken soup.
- Wow. We've got so much food.

262
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,567
It's like Ma'am Felma
and Sir Manuel just got married.

263
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:11,267
Wow! They even went on their
honeymoon first!

264
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,000
Are you jealous, Miss?

265
00:18:14,133 --> 00:18:18,267
Why would I be?
Every day is a honeymoon.

266
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:21,133
I can imagine.

267
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,133
TMI!

268
00:18:23,267 --> 00:18:26,933
- You know, that's why...
- Hey, stop. Put it here.

269
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:30,667
There.

270
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,167
Your Uncle Abel just texted.
They've landed.

271
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:35,933
I'm just praying

272
00:18:37,067 --> 00:18:39,767
that Mom doesn't get mad
about what you did, Coleen.

273
00:18:45,433 --> 00:18:47,833
That turbulence was crazy.

274
00:18:47,967 --> 00:18:49,767
- Probably the weather, bro.
- Yeah.

275
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,767
It honestly scared me a bit.

276
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:56,867
Felma, are you not feeling well?
Are you okay?

277
00:18:58,067 --> 00:19:01,033
I've got a bit of a headache.

278
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:02,833
But I'm okay.

279
00:19:04,867 --> 00:19:06,267
I'm just going to the restroom.

280
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:10,033
Noah and I will head
to the car first

281
00:19:10,167 --> 00:19:11,867
to cool it down with the AC.

282
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:12,900
Okay.

283
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:15,000
I'll stay with Felma for now.

284
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:16,567
- Sure, bro.
- Yeah.

285
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,367
Over there.

286
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:22,533
I'll go with you.

287
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:24,367
You'll come with me?

288
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:26,300
Inside?

289
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:28,133
If you want. If it's possible.

290
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:32,033
Hey! You're so naughty.
Just wait for me, okay?

291
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:34,433
Alright.

292
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,667
Bro, let's load the luggage
first.

293
00:19:40,800 --> 00:19:41,700
Yeah, sure.

294
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:43,800
There.

295
00:20:10,633 --> 00:20:12,067
They're taking a long time.

296
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,500
Yeah, they are.

297
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:39,067
Miss,

298
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,200
can I ask a favor?

299
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:43,533
Can you check if my wife
is inside?

300
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:44,933
She's not feeling well.

301
00:20:45,067 --> 00:20:46,267
Her name's Felma.

302
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:48,700
- Okay, please wait a moment.
- Thank you.

303
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:51,167
Felma?

304
00:20:51,300 --> 00:20:52,533
Felma?

305
00:20:58,367 --> 00:21:00,467
Sir, there's no Felma inside.

306
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,600
Are you sure?

307
00:21:01,733 --> 00:21:03,567
Yes, Sir. There are only two
women in there.

308
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:05,600
Neither of them is named Felma.

309
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:13,800
They're taking so long.

310
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:15,033
Yeah, they are.

311
00:21:16,933 --> 00:21:18,800
There's Manuel.

312
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,867
Why isn't Felma with him?

313
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:26,167
Did Felma come here?

314
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:28,667
Manuel, weren't you with Felma?

315
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:29,933
Where is she?

316
00:21:30,067 --> 00:21:31,633
She's missing.

317
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,367
I waited outside the restroom
for so long,

318
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,600
then I had it checked.

319
00:21:34,733 --> 00:21:35,867
She wasn't there anymore.

320
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:42,467
Felma might come here, Abel.
Wait here, okay?

321
00:21:42,633 --> 00:21:46,167
Manuel, let's go back inside.
Let's look for her there.

322
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:17,100
We need to find her right away.
She's sick.

323
00:22:17,267 --> 00:22:18,433
It's dangerous for her
to be alone.

324
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:20,833
Okay, Sir.
I'll alert the others.

325
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:22,200
Felma!

326
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:23,333
Felma!

327
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:24,867
Dad, why would Mom do that?

328
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,300
Son, I honestly don't know.

329
00:22:26,433 --> 00:22:29,467
Let's just work together and
find her as soon as possible.

330
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:31,767
Could someone have
threatened Mom

331
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:33,800
to make her stay away from you?

332
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:36,500
Wait, bro.

333
00:22:36,633 --> 00:22:37,733
Bro, hold on.

334
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:39,867
Why?

335
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,800
I can't move my leg.

336
00:22:41,933 --> 00:22:43,300
Did it ever occur to you

337
00:22:43,433 --> 00:22:46,133
that Hazel might've found out
Mom was coming home today?

338
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:48,633
If you hadn't messed with
the restraining order,

339
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:50,033
we'd be fine!

340
00:22:50,167 --> 00:22:51,700
You had it lifted!

341
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:53,033
Wait!

342
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:54,833
This is crazy.

343
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,067
Just a second.

344
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,467
I'm coming!
